This paper discusses differential privacy in the context of machine learning, specifically regression models. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of their approach on privacy attacks, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
